The code doesn't seem to set the title to a valid arabic word.

cwaBar.getTitle( ).getLabel( ).getCaption( ).setValue( " vsl fdhkn" );

Is this suppose to be arabic?

The problem here is that the text is not encoded properly in the javacode.  It should be encoded using UTF-8.

I added the following code to set the chart title.  Note I encode the string to UTF-8.

		String st = new String(" ");
		try {
			String encode = new String(st.getBytes(), "UTF-8");
			// Title
			cwaBar.getTitle( ).getLabel( ).getCaption( ).setValue(encode); //$NON-NLS-1$
		} catch (UnsupportedEncodingException e) {
			// TODO Auto-generated catch block
			e.printStackTrace();
		}

The problem is that the default font installed on your system does not display arabic text properly.  Note: If a font is not specified the SVG renderer uses the default font.  

You can force the font to use another font that supports arabic glyphs as follows:

FontDefinition fd = cwaBar.getTitle( ).getLabel( ).getCaption( ).getFont();
fd.setName("Arial");

